==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: high chair
<hw>high" chair`</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>a chair designed for feeding a very young child, having four long
legs and a footrest and a detachable tray, which rests in front of the
child, holds the food, and also serves as a restraint, to keep the child
from falling out of the chair.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> feeding chair.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

